@startuml agent-gateway-comms
' Every call in and out of an agent container, and what authenticates each one.
' Source of truth: docs/src/runtime/contract.md
!include _style.puml

' The notes below are hand-wrapped; raise the wrap width so those line
' breaks are honoured rather than re-wrapped raggedly at 220px.
skinparam wrapWidth 340

participant "**kubelet**\n(node component)" as kubelet $mutedBg

box "a user namespace" #FCFCFC
  participant "**Agent** container\nserves $KAALM_HEALTH_PORT\n(default 8080)" as agent $agentBg
  participant "**AgentTask**\ncontainer" as task $agentBg
end box

participant "**Gateway**\n:8443 LLM listener" as gw $gwBg
participant "**Controller**" as ctrl $ctrlBg

note over agent
  One cert, both directions:
  **$KAALM_TLS_CERT** is the **server**
  cert below and the **client** cert on
  every call to the gateway. Peers are
  verified against $KAALM_CA_CERT.
end note

== Inbound: two auth regimes on the one port ==

kubelet -[#9E9E9E]> agent : GET /readyz, GET /livez\nHTTPS, **no client cert**
agent -[#9E9E9E]-> kubelet : 200 when healthy

gw -[#1B5E20]> agent : POST /v1/message\nmTLS, gateway presents its client cert
alt no peer certificate
  agent -[#B71C1C]-> gw : 401 Unauthorized
else SAN is not the gateway Service DNS
  agent -[#B71C1C]-> gw : 403 Forbidden
else SAN matches
  agent -[#1B5E20]-> gw : 200 response envelope
end

note over kubelet, task
  **Why enforcement is per path, not per handshake.**
  The cert-less probes and the cert-required /v1/message
  share $KAALM_HEALTH_PORT, so the socket must
  **request** a client cert without **requiring** one:
  ClientAuth = **VerifyClientCertIfGiven**.
  RequireAndVerifyClientCert would fail every probe at the
  handshake, before the router ran, leaving the agent
  permanently unready. So the 401/403 above are decided at
  the handler instead. The controller :9443 and gateway
  :8443 listeners use this same pattern.
end note

== Outbound to $KAALM_GATEWAY_ENDPOINT: mTLS only ==

agent -[#4A148C]> gw : LLM request\nmTLS, client cert $KAALM_TLS_CERT\nSAN {name}.{ns}.svc.cluster.local
agent -[#4A148C]> gw : POST /v1/agent/heartbeat\nmTLS, **Agents only**
task -[#4A148C]> gw : POST /v1/task/complete\nmTLS, **AgentTasks only**

note over gw
  No bearer-token fallback on the two
  report paths. The listener admits
  either SAN shape; the handler splits
  by workload kind. An AgentTask cert on
  /v1/agent/heartbeat, or an Agent cert
  on /v1/task/complete, gets
  **403 access_denied**.
end note

== Controller to gateway: dialed by Pod IP, not $KAALM_GATEWAY_ENDPOINT ==

ctrl -[#0D47A1]> gw : GET /v1/activity?namespace=\nmTLS, **controller SAN required**
gw -[#0D47A1]-> ctrl : in-memory activity timestamps\n(no etcd writes per request)

legend bottom
  Grey = no client cert | Purple = agent mTLS | Green = gateway mTLS | Blue = controller mTLS
endlegend
@enduml
